    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Worldly pleasures are infatuating; and for their momentary enjoyment many sacrifice the friendship of Heaven, with the peace, love, and joy that it affords. But these chosen objects of delight soon become disgusting, unsatisfying.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 1-29-1884\" data-link=\"821.5211\">The Review and Herald, January 29, 1884</span>.</span></a></sup>",
