    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 521.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The exciting amusements of our time keep the minds of men and women, but more especially the youth, in a fever of excitement, which is telling upon their stock of vitality in a far greater degree than all their studies and physical labors, and have a tendency to dwarf the intellect and corrupt the morals.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"HR 12-1-1872\" data-link=\"504.710\">The Health Reformer, December, 1872</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 1638,
    "translations": [
      {
