    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 522.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Among Pleasure Lovers Are Many Church Members</strong>&mdash;Many are eagerly participating in worldly, demoralizing amusements which God&apos;s word forbids. Thus they sever their connection with God and rank themselves with the pleasure lovers of the world. The sins that destroyed the antediluvians and the cities of the plain exist today&mdash;not merely in heathen lands, not only among popular professors of Christianity, but with some who profess to be looking for the coming of the Son of man. If God should present these sins before you as they appear in His sight, you would be filled with shame and terror.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"5T 218.1\" data-link=\"113.1120\">Ibid., 5:218</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 1640,
