    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Satan, a Skillful Charmer</strong>&mdash;The young generally conduct themselves as though the precious hours of probation, while mercy lingers, were one grand holiday and they were placed in this world merely for their own amusement, to be gratified with a continued round of excitement. Satan has been making special efforts to lead them to find happiness in worldly amusements and to justify themselves by endeavoring to show that these amusements are harmless, innocent, and even important for health.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">8<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"1T 501.1\" data-link=\"116.2337\">Testimonies for the Church 1:501</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 1642,
    "translations": [
