    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 523.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "He [Satan] presents the path of holiness as difficult, while the paths of worldly pleasure are strewn with flowers. In false and flattering colors he arrays the world with its pleasures before the youth. But the pleasures of earth will soon come to an end, and that which is sown must also be reaped.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"YI 1-1-1907.4\" data-link=\"469.5578\">The Youth&apos;s Instructor, January 1, 1907</span>.</span></a></sup>",
    "puborder": 1643,
